<article class="clearfix single-box entry-content">
<p><br />
When you combine the exquisite designing styling’s of the one of Germany’s premier automobile makers i.e. Mercedes, with one of their leading airlines i.e. Lufthansa, you get a super luxury airliner whose interiors are as fabulous as a high-end suite at a five star hotel and as futuristic as something out of a Sci-Fi movie. According to Mercedes-Benz Style and Lufthansa, these new uber luxurious airplane cabin concepts have been designed specifically for those medium to long haul flights, but if you can afford it, even a short trip could be just as lavish.<br />
<span id="more-126163"></span><br />
<figure id="attachment_126167" style="width: 690px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img alt="Virtually seamless ceiling to floor construct; great use of available space" width="690" height="388" data-srcset="https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-2-690x388.jpg 690w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-2-300x169.jpg 300w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-2-330x186.jpg 330w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-2.jpg 970w" sizes="(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px" data-src="https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-2-690x388.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-126167 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" /><noscript><img src="https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-2-690x388.jpg" alt="Virtually seamless ceiling to floor construct; great use of available space" width="690" height="388" class="size-large wp-image-126167" srcset="https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-2-690x388.jpg 690w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-2-300x169.jpg 300w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-2-330x186.jpg 330w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-2.jpg 970w" sizes="(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px" /></noscript><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Virtually seamless ceiling to floor construct; great use of available space</figcaption></figure><br />
One of the first things you’ll notice is the versatile use of pace which is unlike anything we’ve seen so far when it comes to plane cabins; the virtually seamless flowing of the ceilings, into the wall and then into the floor gives it a slightly “tube-ish” sort of look and does tend to give the entire cabin a very clean cut and highly refined look. The beautifully crafted furniture showcased in the concept renderings give the cabin a very roomy motif especially with the nestled, very elegant and comfortable chairs and other seating areas. It looks like there’s ample space to move around comfortably without bumping into anything.</p>
<div style="clear:both; margin-top:0em; margin-bottom:0em;"><a href="https://luxurylaunches.com/transport/flexjet_launches_limited_edition_luxury_travel_program.php" target="_self" class="u13c93fdd823be152154d39b1ab875789" data-wpel-link="internal"><style> .u13c93fdd823be152154d39b1ab875789 { padding:0px; margin: 0; padding-top:1em!important; padding-bottom:1em!important; width:100%; display: block; font-weight:bold; background-color:#FFFFFF; border:0!important; border-left:4px solid #FFFFFF!important; text-decoration:none; } .u13c93fdd823be152154d39b1ab875789:active, .u13c93fdd823be152154d39b1ab875789:hover { opacity: 1; transition: opacity 250ms; webkit-transition: opacity 250ms; text-decoration:none; } .u13c93fdd823be152154d39b1ab875789 { transition: background-color 250ms; webkit-transition: background-color 250ms; opacity: 1; transition: opacity 250ms; webkit-transition: opacity 250ms; } .u13c93fdd823be152154d39b1ab875789 .ctaText { font-weight:bold; color:inherit; text-decoration:none; font-size: 16px; } .u13c93fdd823be152154d39b1ab875789 .postTitle { color:#000000; text-decoration: underline!important; font-size: 16px; } .u13c93fdd823be152154d39b1ab875789:hover .postTitle { text-decoration: underline!important; } </style><div style="padding-left:1em; padding-right:1em;"><span class="ctaText">READ:</span>&nbsp; <span class="postTitle">Flexjet launches limited edition luxury travel program</span></div></a></div><p><figure id="attachment_126169" style="width: 690px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img alt="Integrated touchscreen panels for access to in-flight services" width="690" height="404" data-srcset="https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-6-690x404.jpg 690w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-6-300x176.jpg 300w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-6-330x193.jpg 330w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-6.jpg 818w" sizes="(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px" data-src="https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-6-690x404.jpg" class="size-large wp-image-126169 lazyload" src="data:image/gif;base64,R0lGODlhAQABAAAAACH5BAEKAAEALAAAAAABAAEAAAICTAEAOw==" /><noscript><img src="https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-6-690x404.jpg" alt="Integrated touchscreen panels for access to in-flight services" width="690" height="404" class="size-large wp-image-126169" srcset="https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-6-690x404.jpg 690w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-6-300x176.jpg 300w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-6-330x193.jpg 330w, https://luxurylaunches.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/mercedes-benz-lufthansa-jet-6.jpg 818w" sizes="(max-width: 690px) 100vw, 690px" /></noscript><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Integrated touchscreen panels for access to in-flight services</figcaption></figure><br />
Other features include longer windows that can be electronically controlled to darken when required, similar to Mercedes’ “Magic Sky” technology that is apparent in the Mercedes-Benz S-Class. The company also aims to have options all over for digital touchscreen displays integrated into the paneling or the surfaces for easy access to all kinds of goodies, we image. </p>
